title: Muir Woods National Monument: Animals
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals               Animals         Adult bobcat soaking up the late afternoon sun. National Park Service  Redwood forests are quiet and deeply shaded places in which wildlife may seem rare or absent entirely. It's easy to remain unseen in this dense forest. Then, too, many of the forest creatures are nocturnal. Others live high in the forest canopy or in the soil or deep duff on the forest floor. In fact, redwood forests are surprisingly lively places. Visit some of our animal links below or check out the Wildlife Checklist to learn more about these elusive forest creatures... Birds Fish Invertebrates
